\chapter{Command-Line Interface}
\label{cli}

The [[learnlog]] command lets teachers and teaching assistants
review the development logs that students produce.
It provides six subcommands: [[list]] gives a compact overview of
the recorded commits, [[export]] creates a portable bundle of the
log, [[set-remote]] and [[push]] configure and deliver the log to
a remote Git repository, [[git]] forwards Git commands to the log
repository, and [[play]] gives an interactive viewer for browsing
the commit history.

We use Typer for the CLI framework because it gives us type-checked
arguments with minimal boilerplate, and the modern
[[Annotated]] style makes the parameter declarations self-documenting.


