\section{Resolving the working directory}

Several commands ([[export]], [[set-remote]], [[push]]) accept an
optional [[-C]] / [[--dir]] argument that points at the project
directory.
When omitted, they search upward from the current directory using
[[find_learnlog_dir]] (defined in the core module, \cref{learnlog}).
Rather than duplicate this pattern in every command, we centralise it
in a helper that either resolves the explicit path or falls back to
the search.

<<helper functions>>=
def resolve_workdir(directory=None):
    """Locate the working directory containing ``.learnlog/``.

    If ``directory`` is given, verifies that it contains a
    ``.learnlog/`` subdirectory.  Otherwise, searches upward
    from the current working directory.
    """
    if directory is None:
        workdir = find_learnlog_dir()
        if workdir is None:
            raise SystemExit(
                "No .learnlog/ directory found."
            )
        return workdir

    workdir = pathlib.Path(directory).resolve()
    if not (workdir / ".learnlog").is_dir():
        raise SystemExit(
            f"No .learnlog/ directory in {workdir}"
        )
    return workdir
@

